<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-01-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-01-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="277" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d277">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Egan</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-01-13"><hi rend="italic">January 13,
                            1892</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Blaine asks whether the promotor fiscal in one of the five points made by
                        him, viz, the third, says that the evidence of the officers and crew of the
                            <hi rend="italic">Baltimore</hi> has been thrown out because
                        conflicting, as Capt. Evans of the <hi rend="italic">Yorktown</hi>
                        telegraphs.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>